1
00:00:14,933 --> 00:00:17,567
Mama Rina, you have
to be strong, okay?

2
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:20,833
Why is Amanda doing this to me?

3
00:00:20,967 --> 00:00:24,467
She's to blame. But she's making
it look like I'm the bad guy.

4
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:26,167
Don't worry. We'll talk
to our lawyer.

5
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:27,567
We'll get you out of here, okay?

6
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:29,100
Do everything you can.

7
00:00:29,233 --> 00:00:31,167
I can't stay another day here.

8
00:00:31,300 --> 00:00:32,367
I'm going to die here, Red.

9
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:35,033
I don't like this place.
I can't stay here.

10
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:37,267
Drop the case against Mama Rina

11
00:00:37,400 --> 00:00:39,533
while I still have some respect
for you.

12
00:00:39,667 --> 00:00:42,367
I'm not the one who
put her in jail.

13
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:44,733
The police caught her
in the act.

14
00:00:44,867 --> 00:00:46,767
She's been doing illegal
business.

15
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:48,233
She got caught only now.

16
00:00:48,367 --> 00:00:50,000
She's lending money and coercing
the people

17
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:51,767
who owe her to pay up.

18
00:00:51,900 --> 00:00:54,467
And unfortunately,
some of them were killed.

19
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:55,633
You're a liar.

20
00:00:55,767 --> 00:00:56,767
See?

21
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:58,667
She thinks I'm the bad guy now.

22
00:00:58,800 --> 00:01:01,067
I don't think I can still reason
with her.

23
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:03,300
Just give Eden more time.

24
00:01:03,433 --> 00:01:06,433
And contemplate if what you're
doing is right.

25
00:01:06,567 --> 00:01:08,267
Rina is a horrible person.

26
00:01:08,433 --> 00:01:10,667
That's not true.

27
00:01:10,800 --> 00:01:13,133
Amanda's accusing me
of something I didn't do.

28
00:01:13,267 --> 00:01:14,700
You set my wife up!

29
00:01:14,833 --> 00:01:17,267
You still don't know that
your wife is a hustler.

30
00:01:17,400 --> 00:01:18,667
She's a loan shark.

31
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:20,567
She lends money with high
interest.

32
00:01:20,700 --> 00:01:24,933
If the client can't pay back
what he owes us,

33
00:01:25,067 --> 00:01:28,267
we take lives as payment.

34
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:31,233
Now you know what will happen
to you if you don't pay me back.

35
00:01:31,367 --> 00:01:34,733
Why don't you just let fate
take place?

36
00:01:34,867 --> 00:01:37,633
Let Rina get her punishment
at the right time.

37
00:01:37,767 --> 00:01:40,433
And just wait for Eden to come
back of her own will.

38
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,167
I can't just wait here

39
00:01:42,300 --> 00:01:44,200
and accept what fate
will throw at me.

40
00:01:44,333 --> 00:01:45,267
I'm going to fight.

41
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:48,367
I'll do something to get
my daughter back.

42
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:51,000
Victor, did you bring
the money to bail me out?

43
00:01:51,133 --> 00:01:52,167
Victor!

44
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:54,067
- Dad!
- What's the matter?

45
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:56,133
How could you do this to us?

46
00:01:56,267 --> 00:01:58,467
I don't know what you're talking
about, Victor.

47
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:00,067
You're lending money illegally.

48
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,933
You're hurting people.

49
00:02:02,067 --> 00:02:03,767
You're evil.

50
00:02:03,900 --> 00:02:06,000
I am shocked too.

51
00:02:06,133 --> 00:02:08,133
How can she do something
like that?

52
00:02:08,267 --> 00:02:11,267
Your mom was right.

53
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:13,467
- Get out of the way. No!
- Let go of her.

54
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,700
I'm taking my daughter away
from your family.

55
00:02:15,867 --> 00:02:18,067
I'm sorry, Mom, but I'm not
coming with you.

56
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:19,700
Don't you care about me anymore?

57
00:02:19,833 --> 00:02:22,500
I can't forget every good thing
she did for me

58
00:02:22,633 --> 00:02:24,367
when you abandoned me.

59
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:29,700
Mama Rina might be unpleasant to
others, but she's a good mother.

60
00:02:29,833 --> 00:02:32,800
And a good wife.

61
00:02:32,933 --> 00:02:34,533
I'm not coming with you.

62
00:02:34,667 --> 00:02:35,900
I think it's clear now.

63
00:02:36,033 --> 00:02:39,667
We're more of a family to her
than you.

64
00:02:47,867 --> 00:02:52,300
Knowing Amanda, she might
sue us for kidnapping.

65
00:02:52,433 --> 00:02:56,433
She will do everything
for revenge.

66
00:02:56,567 --> 00:02:58,600
But I stayed with Red
of my own will.

67
00:02:58,733 --> 00:03:00,900
He didn't force me.

68
00:03:01,033 --> 00:03:05,333
Yenyen is not a minor anymore,
Mom.

69
00:03:05,467 --> 00:03:07,767
But we have no legal ties
to her.

70
00:03:07,900 --> 00:03:12,733
Unless, of course,
you two get married.

71
00:03:12,867 --> 00:03:16,267
But up until that time...

72
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:18,300
Amanda is still
your legal guardian.

73
00:03:18,433 --> 00:03:20,600
Because she is your parent.

74
00:03:27,900 --> 00:03:29,933
Red?

75
00:03:30,067 --> 00:03:31,467
Red, I've been looking for you.

76
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:33,967
I thought we were going
to sleep?

77
00:03:50,267 --> 00:03:51,767
That's strange.

78
00:03:54,533 --> 00:04:00,700
We were better off when
we were on the island.

79
00:04:00,833 --> 00:04:07,367
Now that we're back, it's like
our problem never ends...

80
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:11,600
like how your mom barged
in here earlier.

81
00:04:11,733 --> 00:04:15,633
My mom was right.

82
00:04:15,767 --> 00:04:18,233
I was thinking the same thing.

83
00:04:18,367 --> 00:04:20,500
She wants to separate us.

84
00:04:24,900 --> 00:04:29,133
I realized that she was right.

85
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:35,433
I don't have a right over you
because I'm no one important.

86
00:04:35,567 --> 00:04:38,300
I'm just your boyfriend,
and she's your mom.

87
00:04:38,433 --> 00:04:40,600
But she doesn't own me.

88
00:04:40,733 --> 00:04:44,500
It's up to me to decide
who I'll be with.

89
00:04:44,633 --> 00:04:47,500
Although you have no legal
rights to me,

90
00:04:47,633 --> 00:04:49,967
we love each other.

91
00:04:50,100 --> 00:04:54,967
And that's what's giving us
the right to be with each other.

92
00:04:55,100 --> 00:04:58,000
No one can stop us now.

93
00:04:58,133 --> 00:05:00,867
Even though we're going
through a rough patch,

94
00:05:01,033 --> 00:05:05,967
Yen, I think it's
the right time.

95
00:05:06,100 --> 00:05:08,100
Let's get married.

96
00:05:08,233 --> 00:05:10,700
So they can't separate us again.

97
00:05:20,333 --> 00:05:21,667
Red, you're right.

98
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:25,200
Even though we're going
through tough times,

99
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:27,833
love doesn't need
the right timing.

100
00:05:30,233 --> 00:05:33,100
I already said yes before.

101
00:05:33,233 --> 00:05:34,533
And now I'm saying yes again.

102
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:38,767
I will marry you wherever you
want, whenever you want.

103
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:42,567
I don't want to be away
from you ever again, Yen.

104
00:05:42,700 --> 00:05:44,567
No one can stop us now, Red.

105
00:05:45,667 --> 00:05:47,433
Even our parents can't stop us.

106
00:05:49,433 --> 00:05:51,800
We love each other.

107
00:05:51,933 --> 00:05:55,633
It's just our parents
who don't get along.

108
00:05:55,767 --> 00:05:59,833
And they don't have to live
together. Only the two of us.

109
00:05:59,967 --> 00:06:02,567
They can't separate
us anymore, Red.

110
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:05,233
I promise.

111
00:06:05,367 --> 00:06:07,400
Not even death.

112
00:06:07,567 --> 00:06:09,033
I love you so much.

113
00:06:10,633 --> 00:06:12,567
I love you so much.

114
00:06:41,100 --> 00:06:43,000
You have a lot of nerve
to do this.

115
00:06:43,133 --> 00:06:44,933
You set my wife up!

116
00:06:45,067 --> 00:06:47,600
You still don't know your wife
so well. She's a loan shark.

117
00:06:47,733 --> 00:06:50,900
She lends money with high
interest.

118
00:06:51,033 --> 00:06:54,200
And if the client doesn't
pay what he owes...

119
00:06:54,333 --> 00:06:56,533
Do you think I'll believe you?

120
00:06:56,667 --> 00:06:58,300
I've known Rina for a while now.

121
00:06:58,433 --> 00:07:02,900
If the client can't pay
what he owes us...

122
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:06,100
we take lives for payment.

123
00:07:06,233 --> 00:07:10,400
Now you know what will happen
to you if you don't pay me.

124
00:07:10,533 --> 00:07:14,167
It's not my intention
to become a loan shark.

125
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:16,033
Our business was doing well
at first.

126
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,100
We were loaning money.

127
00:07:17,233 --> 00:07:20,100
But it's Zandro's fault!

128
00:07:20,233 --> 00:07:23,633
We got addicted to it because
we were making a lot of money.

129
00:07:23,767 --> 00:07:24,800
We were making a lot of money.

130
00:07:24,933 --> 00:07:27,133
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

131
00:07:46,867 --> 00:07:48,700
Dad.

132
00:07:48,867 --> 00:07:50,567
Drinking won't help.

133
00:07:53,933 --> 00:08:02,300
Red, I just want to forget
for a little bit.

134
00:08:02,433 --> 00:08:07,333
I still can't believe that your
mom did things behind my back.

135
00:08:07,467 --> 00:08:08,800
She was living a double life.

136
00:08:10,933 --> 00:08:17,900
You know, I've been telling her
to stay away from Zandro.

137
00:08:18,933 --> 00:08:21,133
He brings us nothing
but trouble.

138
00:08:21,300 --> 00:08:23,833
Look at what he did.

139
00:08:23,967 --> 00:08:25,833
He left her behind.

140
00:08:25,967 --> 00:08:28,167
He's gone.

141
00:08:28,300 --> 00:08:31,067
He's nowhere to be seen.

142
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:39,067
Even if Mom did horrible things,
she's still family.

143
00:08:40,733 --> 00:08:45,700
I can't abandon her no matter
what happens.

144
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:50,067
I hope...

145
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:51,567
I hope you feel the same.

146
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:54,567
Dad, she's your wife.

147
00:08:57,300 --> 00:08:59,633
You made a vow
when you married her.

148
00:09:03,400 --> 00:09:05,400
I'm sorry.

149
00:09:05,533 --> 00:09:06,900
I'm so confused.

150
00:09:08,933 --> 00:09:11,100
I thought I knew your mom.

151
00:09:11,233 --> 00:09:13,300
She betrayed me.

152
00:09:13,433 --> 00:09:15,000
That's what hurts.

153
00:09:15,133 --> 00:09:21,567
Even if she did unpleasant
things,

154
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:23,867
she still deserves
a second chance.

155
00:09:28,233 --> 00:09:29,900
You still love her, don't you?

156
00:09:32,733 --> 00:09:33,700
Of course, Red.

157
00:09:34,733 --> 00:09:36,267
I still love your mom.

158
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:39,367
I still love our family.

159
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:43,533
We're just going through
a trial.

160
00:09:43,667 --> 00:09:44,933
We'll get through this.

161
00:09:45,933 --> 00:09:47,767
Our family can overcome this.

162
00:09:51,233 --> 00:09:53,067
Yes, Red.

163
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:55,033
We can get through this.

164
00:09:56,400 --> 00:10:00,333
This hardship won't ruin
our family.

165
00:10:02,867 --> 00:10:07,567
In fact, it will strengthen
our family's bond.

166
00:10:10,467 --> 00:10:12,133
Thank you, son.

167
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:22,633
Are you serious? You and Red
are getting married?

168
00:10:22,767 --> 00:10:23,467
Raichu, you're too loud!

169
00:10:24,433 --> 00:10:26,200
Are you announcing it
to the whole campus?

170
00:10:26,333 --> 00:10:27,600
My gosh.

171
00:10:27,733 --> 00:10:29,833
I'm just so happy for you!

172
00:10:29,967 --> 00:10:30,967
I knew it!

173
00:10:31,100 --> 00:10:32,433
The two of you are meant
for each other.

174
00:10:32,567 --> 00:10:36,200
You're like Romeo and Juliet.

175
00:10:36,367 --> 00:10:37,467
My gosh!

176
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:43,767
I thought Red and I would break
up after we lost our baby.

177
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:46,633
But after everything
we've been through,

178
00:10:46,767 --> 00:10:53,700
those struggles
made us stronger.

179
00:10:53,833 --> 00:10:55,433
Wait a minute!

180
00:10:55,567 --> 00:10:57,567
How are you going
to get married?

181
00:10:57,700 --> 00:10:59,733
Didn't you say that your
Mama Rina is in jail?

182
00:10:59,867 --> 00:11:00,967
And what about your mom?

183
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:02,633
Is she going to attend
the wedding?

184
00:11:02,767 --> 00:11:06,333
We're going to wait for Mama
Rina to get out of jail.

185
00:11:06,467 --> 00:11:08,867
She can make bail.

186
00:11:09,033 --> 00:11:11,100
And my mom...

187
00:11:11,233 --> 00:11:13,967
I'm not sure.

188
00:11:14,100 --> 00:11:17,167
She still doesn't like Red.

189
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:19,367
She doesn't want us
to be together.

190
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:23,433
So even though it's hard for me
not to have her at my wedding...

191
00:11:23,567 --> 00:11:25,800
I'll just endure it.

192
00:11:25,933 --> 00:11:29,267
So, can't you still forgive her?

193
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:31,367
Of course, I want
to forgive her.

194
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:34,133
But not right now.

195
00:11:34,267 --> 00:11:36,167
She hates Red's family.

196
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:38,100
But you know what?

197
00:11:38,233 --> 00:11:41,900
I pray every day that everything
will be all right.

198
00:11:42,067 --> 00:11:45,100
I hope our family will get along
as one.

199
00:11:47,533 --> 00:11:53,767
It's just sad to think I'll keep
my wedding a secret from my mom.

200
00:11:53,900 --> 00:11:58,467
While other parents dream of
being at their child's wedding.

201
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:01,933
Ramos, you have a visitor.

202
00:12:02,067 --> 00:12:03,567
Who is it? Is it my husband?

203
00:12:03,700 --> 00:12:04,900
Is Victor here?

204
00:12:05,033 --> 00:12:06,367
Or is it my son?

205
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:08,467
Who's here to visit me? Victor?

206
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:09,933
Victor?

207
00:12:10,067 --> 00:12:11,433
Red?

208
00:12:25,900 --> 00:12:33,433
Hola , Rina. So, how's your stay
in jail?

209
00:12:33,567 --> 00:12:36,033
Sit down.

210
00:12:36,167 --> 00:12:38,167
Hola ?

211
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:40,767
Are you now a Latin American?

212
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:45,167
Amanda, in my eyes...

213
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:48,433
you still look dirt poor.

214
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:50,733
Just dirt poor?

215
00:12:50,867 --> 00:12:52,100
You...

216
00:12:52,233 --> 00:12:54,833
You look like dirt.

217
00:12:58,533 --> 00:13:07,500
You experienced the smell
of jail before I did.

218
00:13:07,633 --> 00:13:11,767
A criminal like you will still
smell like an inmate

219
00:13:11,900 --> 00:13:14,933
no matter how fancy
your clothes

220
00:13:15,067 --> 00:13:23,600
or how much expensive
perfume you wear.

221
00:13:23,767 --> 00:13:26,133
That's who you are, Amanda.

222
00:13:26,267 --> 00:13:29,233
But you're a jealous woman.

223
00:13:29,367 --> 00:13:31,667
You're the one who's in jail
right now.

224
00:13:31,800 --> 00:13:35,067
You're the one who smells
like jail.

225
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:37,933
The world really is round,
isn't it?

226
00:13:38,067 --> 00:13:40,967
Now I'm on top.

227
00:13:44,267 --> 00:13:46,867
So, you came here to rub
that in?

228
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,267
Yes.

229
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:52,633
But I got to hand it to you.

230
00:13:52,767 --> 00:13:55,633
That's so much effort.

231
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:57,767
But you're still cheap.

232
00:14:00,433 --> 00:14:05,433
Go ahead. Convince yourself that
what you're saying is true.

233
00:14:05,567 --> 00:14:07,767
But that's all you can do, Rina.

234
00:14:07,900 --> 00:14:12,667
Your words mean nothing
to me anymore.

235
00:14:12,800 --> 00:14:15,033
This is your karma.

236
00:14:15,167 --> 00:14:18,667
And I will make sure you won't
just rot in this jail.

237
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:22,633
You'll die here too.

238
00:14:22,767 --> 00:14:24,667
Is that so?

239
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:28,633
Well, brace yourself
when I get out of here.

240
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:32,933
Because I'll come for you.

241
00:14:33,067 --> 00:14:35,867
I'll be waiting.

242
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:39,133
Because there won't be anything
left for you to come back to.

243
00:14:39,267 --> 00:14:42,533
You ruined your family, Rina.

244
00:14:42,667 --> 00:14:45,533
They'll leave you here to rot.

245
00:14:45,667 --> 00:14:48,100
You're wrong about that, Amanda.

246
00:14:48,233 --> 00:14:49,367
You're the one who doesn't have
a family.

247
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:51,200
You know why?

248
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:54,067
Eden is not coming back to you.

249
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:57,133
Eden is mine now.

250
00:14:57,267 --> 00:15:00,300
You have no one.

251
00:15:00,433 --> 00:15:02,733
Your daughter's gone.

252
00:15:02,900 --> 00:15:06,433
She's coming home to me now.

253
00:15:06,567 --> 00:15:08,633
You don't have Eden anymore.

254
00:15:08,767 --> 00:15:09,867
She's mine now.

255
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,600
Do you hear me?

256
00:15:11,733 --> 00:15:14,600
Hey, I'm not done yet.
You have to listen to me.

257
00:15:14,733 --> 00:15:16,933
You have no one to go home to.

258
00:15:17,067 --> 00:15:18,967
No daughter.

259
00:15:19,100 --> 00:15:24,933
Eden is all mine. I pity you.
Poor Amanda.

260
00:15:25,067 --> 00:15:28,100
You're all alone.

261
00:15:28,233 --> 00:15:29,967
Talk to the hand.

262
00:15:41,933 --> 00:15:44,167
Thank you, Victor.

263
00:15:44,300 --> 00:15:48,167
Thank you for visiting me.

264
00:15:48,300 --> 00:15:51,700
That awful woman, Amanda,

265
00:15:51,833 --> 00:15:55,433
told me that you guys
abandoned me.

266
00:15:57,533 --> 00:16:01,067
That I ruined our family.

267
00:16:04,633 --> 00:16:06,967
Are you still mad at me?

268
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:12,833
Haven't you forgiven me yet?

269
00:16:12,967 --> 00:16:14,900
When we married,

270
00:16:15,033 --> 00:16:21,433
I promised I'd stay with you
for better or worse.

271
00:16:21,567 --> 00:16:24,033
And I will keep that promise.

272
00:16:24,167 --> 00:16:29,200
If I can forgive you, I will...

273
00:16:29,333 --> 00:16:32,233
For Red's sake.

274
00:16:32,367 --> 00:16:35,067
Victor, thank you.

275
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:37,900
Thank you for not abandoning me.

276
00:16:39,967 --> 00:16:45,733
I'm glad you didn't leave me.

277
00:16:45,900 --> 00:16:49,067
Our lawyer made bail already.

278
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:53,300
He's taking care of your release
papers right now.

279
00:16:53,433 --> 00:16:55,433
Thank you, Victor.

280
00:16:55,567 --> 00:16:57,633
I really want to get out
of here.

281
00:16:57,767 --> 00:17:00,133
I'll get scabies
from this place.

282
00:17:00,267 --> 00:17:02,567
I cannot spend another day here.

283
00:17:02,700 --> 00:17:04,333
Do you know how much
it stinks here?

284
00:17:04,467 --> 00:17:06,933
Even the people in
that jail smell.

285
00:17:07,067 --> 00:17:09,267
They stink so bad, Victor.

286
00:17:11,067 --> 00:17:17,467
Don't worry. I promise,
once I get out of here...

287
00:17:17,633 --> 00:17:21,533
I'm going to change my ways.

288
00:17:21,667 --> 00:17:25,233
I'll be honest with you.

289
00:17:25,367 --> 00:17:28,133
I won't get into the illegal
business anymore.

290
00:17:29,867 --> 00:17:36,433
We'll be honest with each other,
okay?

291
00:17:36,567 --> 00:17:41,567
Let's not hide anything
from each other.

292
00:17:41,700 --> 00:17:43,667
Promise?

293
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:55,100
Honestly, no one knows I have
a financial problem.

294
00:17:55,267 --> 00:17:57,767
I even lied to my wife.

295
00:17:57,900 --> 00:18:01,500
I told her that we were business
partners.

296
00:18:02,533 --> 00:18:06,967
But the truth is,
we're bankrupt.

297
00:18:07,100 --> 00:18:10,333
That's why I need to borrow
money to keep the bank afloat

298
00:18:10,467 --> 00:18:13,667
and not get in trouble
with my clients.

299
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:18,967
Because I lost their money
in a bad investment.

300
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:23,133
You must think I really am weak,
but I just got unlucky.

301
00:18:23,300 --> 00:18:26,500
And don't worry, I won't run
with your money.

302
00:18:26,633 --> 00:18:28,833
I will pay you back
with interest.

303
00:18:28,967 --> 00:18:31,700
Like we agreed upon.

304
00:18:31,833 --> 00:18:34,300
I believe you.

305
00:18:34,433 --> 00:18:36,133
Don't worry.

306
00:18:36,267 --> 00:18:40,000
No one will know about this.

307
00:18:40,133 --> 00:18:41,067
Victor.

308
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:43,900
Victor, can you hear me?

309
00:18:47,033 --> 00:18:49,500
No more secrets, okay?

310
00:18:49,633 --> 00:18:51,233
No more secrets.

311
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:08,900
Lucho!

312
00:19:09,033 --> 00:19:12,333
Rina's out of jail.

313
00:19:12,467 --> 00:19:15,633
She got out on bail!

314
00:19:15,767 --> 00:19:19,000
Her lawyer said she
could get out on bail.

315
00:19:19,133 --> 00:19:20,400
There's nothing we can do
about that.

316
00:19:20,533 --> 00:19:22,333
I can't let that happen!

317
00:19:22,467 --> 00:19:23,933
She only stayed in jail
for one day!

318
00:19:24,067 --> 00:19:25,700
Do something about this.

319
00:19:25,833 --> 00:19:27,900
What do you want us to do?

320
00:19:28,033 --> 00:19:30,867
I want Rina to get beaten up.

321
00:19:31,033 --> 00:19:32,533
Do you need something from me?

322
00:19:32,667 --> 00:19:34,233
Yes, I do.

323
00:19:34,367 --> 00:19:36,900
I just want to sharpen
this on your neck!

324
00:19:46,867 --> 00:19:48,833
Don't try to fight me.

325
00:19:48,967 --> 00:19:51,467
I only want to give you
a souvenir.

326
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:55,667
So you won't be able to forget
about us.

327
00:19:57,567 --> 00:19:58,700
Give her a souvenir.

328
00:19:58,833 --> 00:20:02,900
I want her to have a memorable
time in jail.

329
00:20:03,067 --> 00:20:04,800
We'll get it done.

330
00:20:10,733 --> 00:20:13,567
Are you really getting out
of jail now, Mom?

331
00:20:13,700 --> 00:20:17,300
Your dad already talked
to the lawyers.

332
00:20:17,433 --> 00:20:20,267
I'm glad you can get out
of jail now.

333
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:25,467
I've been praying that they
let you out of jail because...

334
00:20:25,600 --> 00:20:27,767
Because we have something
to tell you.

335
00:20:27,900 --> 00:20:30,300
What is it?

336
00:20:30,433 --> 00:20:32,200
Mom, Dad...

337
00:20:32,333 --> 00:20:34,400
we're getting married.

338
00:20:34,533 --> 00:20:37,067
Oh my God! I'm so happy for you!

339
00:20:37,233 --> 00:20:41,333
But I hope you didn't get
pressured because of me.

340
00:20:41,467 --> 00:20:43,133
Of course not, Mama Rina.

341
00:20:43,267 --> 00:20:45,867
We both wanted to do this.

342
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:49,100
Mama Rina, Papa Victor,
is that okay with you?

343
00:20:49,233 --> 00:20:52,433
Of course! Of course, it's okay!

344
00:20:52,567 --> 00:20:57,933
I'm not selfish
like your mother.

345
00:21:04,867 --> 00:21:07,767
Congratulations.

346
00:21:07,900 --> 00:21:12,533
I'm sorry I can't help you
with the wedding preparations.

347
00:21:12,700 --> 00:21:14,267
No, Mom. It's okay.

348
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:15,367
It's just a small wedding.

349
00:21:15,500 --> 00:21:16,767
A small garden wedding.

350
00:21:16,900 --> 00:21:18,800
It's just going to be
our family.

351
00:21:18,933 --> 00:21:21,400
We just want to get married.

352
00:21:21,533 --> 00:21:23,200
Of course.

353
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:29,833
Amanda, you little wench!

354
00:21:29,967 --> 00:21:32,767
Even if I don't like
your daughter,

355
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:37,233
I will use her to get
my revenge!

356
00:21:37,367 --> 00:21:40,200
You will never get her
back from me.

357
00:21:47,367 --> 00:21:49,167
What now? Are you ready
to beat her up?

358
00:21:49,300 --> 00:21:51,667
Let's go.

359
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:53,467
So you think we're stinky?

360
00:21:55,067 --> 00:21:58,000
You think we didn't overhear
what you said about us?

361
00:22:00,633 --> 00:22:02,433
Now let me hear you say
that we stink!

362
00:22:08,867 --> 00:22:11,800
Listen to me. Don't you ever
tell anyone about this!

363
00:22:11,933 --> 00:22:13,833
Or else I will kill you!

364
00:22:29,633 --> 00:22:33,000
Eden! Why did you put
your gown on?

365
00:22:33,133 --> 00:22:34,333
That's the reason we came here.

366
00:22:34,467 --> 00:22:36,433
To fit my gown, remember?

367
00:22:36,567 --> 00:22:41,633
Eden, the elderlies believe
that wearing your wedding dress

368
00:22:41,767 --> 00:22:44,900
before the wedding
brings bad luck.

369
00:22:45,033 --> 00:22:46,200
I can't let that happen!

370
00:22:46,333 --> 00:22:49,467
Once they're married, I can
never get my daughter back.

371
00:22:49,633 --> 00:22:51,367
You still can't
get her back even

372
00:22:51,500 --> 00:22:52,533
if she's not married to Red.

373
00:22:52,667 --> 00:22:54,767
I won't wait for her to come
home of her own will.

374
00:22:54,900 --> 00:22:56,767
They can't get married.

375
00:22:56,900 --> 00:23:01,433
Yenyen, take this ring
as a sign of my love

376
00:23:01,567 --> 00:23:03,400
and faithfulness to you.

377
00:23:03,533 --> 00:23:09,267
Red, wear this ring as a sign
of my love and fidelity

378
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:11,233
forever and ever.
